    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References>
        <Reference>06000500400008</Reference>
      </References>
      <Content>The occurrence of ἀρχιποίμην ‘chief shepherd’ in {S:06000500400008} is an excellent example of figurative usage. There is no indication that by the time 1 Peter was written ἀρχιποίμην had acquired the conventional meaning of a title designating Christ as one who had principal responsibility for believers. The meaning of ἀρχιποίμην, therefore, is simply ‘chief shepherd,’ but the reference is to Christ in a function which does not involve the literal care of sheep.</Content>
    </Note>
